h3cWIPS.name: h3cWIPS

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

h3cWIPS.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cWIPS.description: This MIB provides information about WIPS feature. Wireless Intrusion Prevention System (WIPS) WIPS is designed to be employed in an area that is serviced by an existing wireless network. It aids in the early detection of malicious outsider attacks and intrusions via wireless networks, and takes corresponding measures in order to guarantee the wireless environment security.

H3cWIPSRadioType.name: H3cWIPSRadioType
H3cWIPSRadioType.description: Represents AP 802.11 radio type of 802.11a/b/g/n as per the standard. The following values are supported: dot11a - 802.11a dot11b - 802.11b dot11g - 802.11g dot11n - 802.11n dot11gn - 802.11gn dot11an - 802.11an

H3cWIPSDevStatus.name: H3cWIPSDevStatus
H3cWIPSDevStatus.description: Represents the status of devices detected by WIPS.

H3cWIPSDevCategoryWay.name: H3cWIPSDevCategoryWay
H3cWIPSDevCategoryWay.description: Represents by which way the device is categorized. 'manual': the device is categorized by user. 'autoByNMS': the device is automatically categorized by NMS(Network Management System). 'autoByDev': the device is automatically categorized by WIPS.

H3cWIPSAPCategoryType.name: H3cWIPSAPCategoryType
H3cWIPSAPCategoryType.description: Represents the categorized type of AP detected by WIPS.

H3cWIPSClientCategoryType.name: H3cWIPSClientCategoryType
H3cWIPSClientCategoryType.description: Represents the categorized type of Client detected by WIPS.

H3cWIPSEncryptMethod.name: H3cWIPSEncryptMethod
H3cWIPSEncryptMethod.description: Represents the frame encryption cipher types for frames on IEEE 802.11 radio interfaces. The MIB defines TC by referring to the 802.11i protocol. The following values are supported: none(1) - clear text or no cipher method is configure, wep(2) - WEP key, tkip(4) - WPA Temporal Key encryption, ccmp(8) - WPA AES CCMP encryption

H3cWIPSAuthMethod.name: H3cWIPSAuthMethod
H3cWIPSAuthMethod.description: Represents the key management mode defined by 802.11i. The following values are supported: none - No key management mode configured, psk - pre-shared key authentication, dot1x - 802.1x authentication. other - other authentication.

H3cWIPSAPClassifyType.name: H3cWIPSAPClassifyType
H3cWIPSAPClassifyType.description: Represents the classify type of AP. 'other' - represents undo operation.

H3cWIPSAPSecurityType.name: H3cWIPSAPSecurityType
H3cWIPSAPSecurityType.description: Represents the AP security type. clear 0x01 wpa2 0x02 wpa 0x04 wep 0x08

h3cWIPSEnable.name: h3cWIPSEnable
h3cWIPSEnable.description: Represents whether the WIPS feature is enabled or not. 'true': enable the WIPS feature. 'false': disable the WIPS feature. WIPS and WIDS feature can not be enabled at the same time.

h3cWIPSSensorLicenseNum.name: h3cWIPSSensorLicenseNum
h3cWIPSSensorLicenseNum.description: Represents the number of sensor license.

h3cWIPSBlocklistAction.name: h3cWIPSBlocklistAction
h3cWIPSBlocklistAction.description: Represents whether the block list feature is enabled or not. 'block' : Enable the block list feature to filter unwanted devices. 'unblock' : Disable the block list feature.

h3cWIPSAPInactiveTime.name: h3cWIPSAPInactiveTime
h3cWIPSAPInactiveTime.description: Represents the time for AP getting inactive.

h3cWIPSSTAInactiveTime.name: h3cWIPSSTAInactiveTime
h3cWIPSSTAInactiveTime.description: Represents the time for STA getting inactive.

h3cWIPSDevAgingTime.name: h3cWIPSDevAgingTime
h3cWIPSDevAgingTime.description: Represents the time for device getting aged.

h3cWIPSStatisticPeriod.name: h3cWIPSStatisticPeriod
h3cWIPSStatisticPeriod.description: Represents the period of WIPS reporting the statistic.

h3cWIPSReclassificationPeriod.name: h3cWIPSReclassificationPeriod
h3cWIPSReclassificationPeriod.description: Represents the period of WIPS reclassifying devices.

h3cWIPSResetAllTrustList.name: h3cWIPSResetAllTrustList
h3cWIPSResetAllTrustList.description: This object is used to remove all entries from the static trust list. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSResetAllBlockList.name: h3cWIPSResetAllBlockList
h3cWIPSResetAllBlockList.description: This object is used to remove all entries from the static block list. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSResetAllIgnoreList.name: h3cWIPSResetAllIgnoreList
h3cWIPSResetAllIgnoreList.description: This object is used to remove all entries from the ignore list. It will return false for get operation..

h3cWIPSResetAllCtmList.name: h3cWIPSResetAllCtmList
h3cWIPSResetAllCtmList.description: This object is used to remove all entries from the static countermeasure list. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSPermitChlBitMap.name: h3cWIPSPermitChlBitMap
h3cWIPSPermitChlBitMap.description: Represents the permit channel number by bitmap.

h3cWIPSVsdTable.name: h3cWIPSVsdTable
h3cWIPSVsdTable.description: The table provides the list of virtual security domain.

h3cWIPSVsdEntry.name: h3cWIPSVsdEntry
h3cWIPSVsdEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each VSD.

h3cWIPSVsdNameCfg.name: h3cWIPSVsdNameCfg
h3cWIPSVsdNameCfg.description: Represents the name of virtual security domain.

h3cWIPSVsdRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSVsdRowStatus
h3cWIPSVsdRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSVsdAtkDctPolicyNameCfg.name: h3cWIPSVsdAtkDctPolicyNameCfg
h3cWIPSVsdAtkDctPolicyNameCfg.description: Represents the name of attack detect policy attached to the VSD.

h3cWIPSRule2VsdTable.name: h3cWIPSRule2VsdTable
h3cWIPSRule2VsdTable.description: The table defines the AP classification rules been attached to the VSD.

h3cWIPSRule2VsdEntry.name: h3cWIPSRule2VsdEntry
h3cWIPSRule2VsdEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each AP classification rule in each VSD.

h3cWIPSRule2VsdAPClaRuleNameCfg.name: h3cWIPSRule2VsdAPClaRuleNameCfg
h3cWIPSRule2VsdAPClaRuleNameCfg.description: Represents the name of AP classification rule attached to the VSD.

h3cWIPSRule2VsdRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSRule2VsdRowStatus
h3cWIPSRule2VsdRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSRule2VsdPrecedence.name: h3cWIPSRule2VsdPrecedence
h3cWIPSRule2VsdPrecedence.description: Represents the precedence of AP classification rule attached to the VSD.

h3cWIPSSensor2VsdTable.name: h3cWIPSSensor2VsdTable
h3cWIPSSensor2VsdTable.description: The table defines the sensor been attached to the VSD.

h3cWIPSSensor2VsdEntry.name: h3cWIPSSensor2VsdEntry
h3cWIPSSensor2VsdEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each sensor in each VSD.

h3cWIPSSensorNameCfg.name: h3cWIPSSensorNameCfg
h3cWIPSSensorNameCfg.description: Represents the name of sensor attached to the VSD.

h3cWIPSSensor2VsdRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSSensor2VsdRowStatus
h3cWIPSSensor2VsdRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSSensorState.name: h3cWIPSSensorState
h3cWIPSSensorState.description: Represents the running state of the sensor. It will return false for set operation.

h3cWIPSSensorRadioTable.name: h3cWIPSSensorRadioTable
h3cWIPSSensorRadioTable.description: The table represents the list of sensor radio information.

h3cWIPSSensorRadioEntry.name: h3cWIPSSensorRadioEntry
h3cWIPSSensorRadioEntry.description: Each entry contains information of a radio of a sensor.

h3cWIPSSensorRadioRadioId.name: h3cWIPSSensorRadioRadioId
h3cWIPSSensorRadioRadioId.description: Represents the radio identifier of the sensor.

h3cWIPSSensorRadioScanMode.name: h3cWIPSSensorRadioScanMode
h3cWIPSSensorRadioScanMode.description: Represents the scanning mode configured to the radio.

h3cWIPSAPClaRuleTable.name: h3cWIPSAPClaRuleTable
h3cWIPSAPClaRuleTable.description: The table defines the parameters for WIPS AP classification rule. One rule could be assigned to different VSDs.

h3cWIPSAPClaRuleEntry.name: h3cWIPSAPClaRuleEntry
h3cWIPSAPClaRuleEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each AP classification rule.

h3cWIPSAPClaRuleName.name: h3cWIPSAPClaRuleName
h3cWIPSAPClaRuleName.description: Represents the name of AP classification rule.

h3cWIPSAPClaRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSAPClaRowStatus
h3cWIPSAPClaRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSAPClaSeverityLevel.name: h3cWIPSAPClaSeverityLevel
h3cWIPSAPClaSeverityLevel.description: Represents the severity level of the AP classification rule. Available value limits from 0 to 100.

h3cWIPSAPClaRuleMatchAll.name: h3cWIPSAPClaRuleMatchAll
h3cWIPSAPClaRuleMatchAll.description: Represents whether match all the AP classification sub-rules which have been configured.

h3cWIPSAPClaType.name: h3cWIPSAPClaType
h3cWIPSAPClaType.description: Represents the type of AP classification.

h3cWIPSAPClaSubRuleSSIDOperator.name: h3cWIPSAPClaSubRuleSSIDOperator
h3cWIPSAPClaSubRuleSSIDOperator.description: Represents the compare way of the SSID in the sub rule, including include/not include/equal/not equal.

h3cWIPSAPClaSubRuleSSIDCase.name: h3cWIPSAPClaSubRuleSSIDCase
h3cWIPSAPClaSubRuleSSIDCase.description: Represents the case sensitive or not for the SSID match. 'true': Case insensitive. 'false': Case sensitive.

h3cWIPSAPClaSubRuleSSID.name: h3cWIPSAPClaSubRuleSSID
h3cWIPSAPClaSubRuleSSID.description: Represents the SSID match template in the ap classification rule.

h3cWIPSSecurityType.name: h3cWIPSSecurityType
h3cWIPSSecurityType.description: Represents the security type of active AP.

h3cWIPSSecurityTypeMatch.name: h3cWIPSSecurityTypeMatch
h3cWIPSSecurityTypeMatch.description: Represents match way of the security type of active AP.

h3cWIPSAPAuthType.name: h3cWIPSAPAuthType
h3cWIPSAPAuthType.description: Represents the authentication type of the AP. undo - represents undo operation

h3cWIPSMaxRSSIValue.name: h3cWIPSMaxRSSIValue
h3cWIPSMaxRSSIValue.description: Represents the high-limit of the RSSI of AP. Available value limits from 1 to 90.

h3cWIPSMinRSSIValue.name: h3cWIPSMinRSSIValue
h3cWIPSMinRSSIValue.description: Represents the low-limit of the RSSI of AP. Available value limits from 0 to 89.

h3cWIPSMaxDuration.name: h3cWIPSMaxDuration
h3cWIPSMaxDuration.description: Represents the high-limit of the duration of AP. Available value limits from 1 to 2592000.

h3cWIPSMinDuration.name: h3cWIPSMinDuration
h3cWIPSMinDuration.description: Represents the low-limit of the duration of AP. Available value limits from 0 to 2591999.

h3cWIPSMaxAPNum.name: h3cWIPSMaxAPNum
h3cWIPSMaxAPNum.description: Represents the high-limit of the number of AP. Available value limits from 1 to 128.

h3cWIPSMinAPNum.name: h3cWIPSMinAPNum
h3cWIPSMinAPNum.description: Represents the low-limit of the number of AP. Available value limits from 0 to 127.

h3cWIPSMaxClientNum.name: h3cWIPSMaxClientNum
h3cWIPSMaxClientNum.description: Represents the high-limit of the number of client. Available value limits from 1 to 128.

h3cWIPSMinClientNum.name: h3cWIPSMinClientNum
h3cWIPSMinClientNum.description: Represents the low-limit of the number of client. Available value limits from 0 to 127.

h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgSupportSet.name: h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgSupportSet
h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgSupportSet.description: Represents the bit string of supported attack detect policy. The specific attack detect policy is supported if its corresponding bit is set to 1; otherwise its corresponding bit is set to 0. bit0: adhoc bit1: ap-spoof bit2: client-spoof bit3: prohibited channel

h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgTable.name: h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgTable
h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgTable.description: The table defines the parameters for WIPS attack detect policy.

h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgEntry.name: h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgEntry
h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each attack detect policy.

h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyName.name: h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyName
h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyName.description: Represents the name of attack detect policy.

h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgRowStatus
h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyCfgRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyBitString.name: h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyBitString
h3cWIPSAtkDctPolicyBitString.description: Represents the bit string of attack detect policy configuration. The specific attack detect policy is enabled if its corresponding bit is set to 1; disabled if its corresponding bit is set to 0. bit0: adhoc bit1: ap-spoof bit2: client-spoof bit3: prohibited channel

h3cWIPSStaticCtmListCfgTable.name: h3cWIPSStaticCtmListCfgTable
h3cWIPSStaticCtmListCfgTable.description: The table provides the MAC address list of devices in the static countermeasure list.

h3cWIPSStaticCtmListCfgEntry.name: h3cWIPSStaticCtmListCfgEntry
h3cWIPSStaticCtmListCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each MAC address in the static countermeasure list.

h3cWIPSStaticCtmListMAC.name: h3cWIPSStaticCtmListMAC
h3cWIPSStaticCtmListMAC.description: Represents the MAC address in static countermeasure list.

h3cWIPSStaticCtmListRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSStaticCtmListRowStatus
h3cWIPSStaticCtmListRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSStaticBlockListCfgTable.name: h3cWIPSStaticBlockListCfgTable
h3cWIPSStaticBlockListCfgTable.description: The table provides the MAC address list of devices in the static block list. WIPS will ignore the frames from the devices in the list, and take the devices as rogue devices.

h3cWIPSStaticBlockListCfgEntry.name: h3cWIPSStaticBlockListCfgEntry
h3cWIPSStaticBlockListCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each MAC address in the static block list.

h3cWIPSStaticBlockListMAC.name: h3cWIPSStaticBlockListMAC
h3cWIPSStaticBlockListMAC.description: Represents the MAC address in static block list.

h3cWIPSStaticBlockListRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSStaticBlockListRowStatus
h3cWIPSStaticBlockListRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSStaticTrustListCfgTable.name: h3cWIPSStaticTrustListCfgTable
h3cWIPSStaticTrustListCfgTable.description: The table provides the MAC address list of devices in the static trust list. WIPS will take the devices in the list as authorized devices.

h3cWIPSStaticTrustListCfgEntry.name: h3cWIPSStaticTrustListCfgEntry
h3cWIPSStaticTrustListCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each MAC address in the static trust list.

h3cWIPSStaticTrustListMAC.name: h3cWIPSStaticTrustListMAC
h3cWIPSStaticTrustListMAC.description: Represents the MAC address in static trust list.

h3cWIPSStaticTrustListRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSStaticTrustListRowStatus
h3cWIPSStaticTrustListRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSIgnoreListCfgTable.name: h3cWIPSIgnoreListCfgTable
h3cWIPSIgnoreListCfgTable.description: The table provides the MAC address list of devices in the ignore list. WIPS will ignore the events caused by the device in the list.

h3cWIPSIgnoreListCfgEntry.name: h3cWIPSIgnoreListCfgEntry
h3cWIPSIgnoreListCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each MAC address in the ignore list.

h3cWIPSIgnoreListMAC.name: h3cWIPSIgnoreListMAC
h3cWIPSIgnoreListMAC.description: Represents the MAC address in ignore list.

h3cWIPSIgnoreListRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSIgnoreListRowStatus
h3cWIPSIgnoreListRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSDctModeTable.name: h3cWIPSDctModeTable
h3cWIPSDctModeTable.description: The table represents the list of AP scanning mode configuration on radio.

h3cWIPSDctModeEntry.name: h3cWIPSDctModeEntry
h3cWIPSDctModeEntry.description: Each entry contains information of WIPS scanning mode on radio.

h3cWIPSDctModeScanMode.name: h3cWIPSDctModeScanMode
h3cWIPSDctModeScanMode.description: Represents the scanning mode. The radio enable-disable status must be disabled before WIPS scanning mode is configured on this radio. The mesh feature must be disabled before any WIPS scanning mode is set on radio. This radio can not apply any service template before the detectOnly scanning mode is set on the radio.

h3cWIPSDctModeRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSDctModeRowStatus
h3cWIPSDctModeRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cWIPSDctAPTable.name: h3cWIPSDctAPTable
h3cWIPSDctAPTable.description: The table represents the list of possible BSS information for APs detected by the WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctAPEntry.name: h3cWIPSDctAPEntry
h3cWIPSDctAPEntry.description: Each entry contains possible BSS information of each AP detected by WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctAPVSD.name: h3cWIPSDctAPVSD
h3cWIPSDctAPVSD.description: Represents the virtual security domain where the BSS was detected.

h3cWIPSDctAPRunningTime.name: h3cWIPSDctAPRunningTime
h3cWIPSDctAPRunningTime.description: Represents the time since AP started to work, which is got from beacon/probe response frame.

h3cWIPSDctAPRunTmLastUpdateTm.name: h3cWIPSDctAPRunTmLastUpdateTm
h3cWIPSDctAPRunTmLastUpdateTm.description: Represents the time update h3cWIPSDctAPRunningTime since system is up.

h3cWIPSDctAPIsCountered.name: h3cWIPSDctAPIsCountered
h3cWIPSDctAPIsCountered.description: Represents whether the detected AP is countered by WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctAPWorkChannel.name: h3cWIPSDctAPWorkChannel
h3cWIPSDctAPWorkChannel.description: Represents the radio channel which the detected AP work on.

h3cWIPSDctAPRadioType.name: h3cWIPSDctAPRadioType
h3cWIPSDctAPRadioType.description: Represents the radio type used by the detected AP.

h3cWIPSDctAPAuthMethod.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAuthMethod
h3cWIPSDctAPAuthMethod.description: Represents the authentication method used by the detected AP. none(1) - No key management mode configured, psk(2) - pre-shared key authentication, dot1x(3) - 802.1x authentication. other(4) - other authentication.

h3cWIPSDctAPEncryptMethod.name: h3cWIPSDctAPEncryptMethod
h3cWIPSDctAPEncryptMethod.description: Represents the encrypt method used by the detected AP. none(1) - clear text or no cipher method is configure, wep(2) - WEP key, tkip(4) - WPA Temporal Key encryption, ccmp(8) - WPA AES CCMP encryption

h3cWIPSDctAPSecurity.name: h3cWIPSDctAPSecurity
h3cWIPSDctAPSecurity.description: Represents the security suites of the detected AP. clear 0x01 wpa2 0x02 wpa 0x04 wep 0x08

h3cWIPSDctAPSeverityLevel.name: h3cWIPSDctAPSeverityLevel
h3cWIPSDctAPSeverityLevel.description: Represents the severity level of the detected AP.

h3cWIPSDctAPLastDctTm.name: h3cWIPSDctAPLastDctTm
h3cWIPSDctAPLastDctTm.description: Represents the time that AP was detected for the last time since system is up.

h3cWIPSDctAPFirstDctTm.name: h3cWIPSDctAPFirstDctTm
h3cWIPSDctAPFirstDctTm.description: Represents the time that AP was detected for the first time since system is up.

h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2BlackList.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2BlackList
h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2BlackList.description: Represents whether the AP will be taken as a rogue AP. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into h3cWIPSBlockListTable and the category of the AP will be taken as rogue. If the value is false, nothing will be done. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2WhiteList.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2WhiteList
h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2WhiteList.description: Represents whether the AP will be taken as an authorized AP. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into h3cWIPSTrustListTable. If the value is false, nothing will be done. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2IgnoreList.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2IgnoreList
h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2IgnoreList.description: Represents whether the AP will be taken as an ignored AP. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into h3cWIPSIgnoreListTable. If the value is false, nothing will be done. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2CtmList.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2CtmList
h3cWIPSDctAPAdd2CtmList.description: Represents whether the AP will be taken as a countered AP. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into h3cWIPSCountermeasureListTable. If the value is false, nothing will be done. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSDctAPCategory.name: h3cWIPSDctAPCategory
h3cWIPSDctAPCategory.description: Represents the categorized result of the AP. For set operation, only the following values are valid: authorized(2),rogue(3),misconfigured(4),external(5)

h3cWIPSDctAPCategoryWay.name: h3cWIPSDctAPCategoryWay
h3cWIPSDctAPCategoryWay.description: Represents by which way the AP is categorized. manual(1) -categorized by user autoByNMS(2) -categorized by NMS(Network Management System) autoByDev(3) -categorized by WIPS

h3cWIPSDctAPStatus.name: h3cWIPSDctAPStatus
h3cWIPSDctAPStatus.description: Represents the status of the AP detected by WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctAPSSID.name: h3cWIPSDctAPSSID
h3cWIPSDctAPSSID.description: Represents the SSID broadcasted by AP.

h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaNum.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaNum
h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaNum.description: Represents the number of clients associated with the detected AP.

h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorNum.name: h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorNum
h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorNum.description: Represents the number of sensors detecting the AP.

h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaTable.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaTable
h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaTable.description: The table represents the list of station associated with APs detected by the WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaEntry.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaEntry
h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaEntry.description: Each entry contains possible station information detected by WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaMac.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaMac
h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaMac.description: Represents the MAC address of station associated with AP.

h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaRowStatus.name: h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaRowStatus
h3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. It will return false for set operation.

h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorTable.name: h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorTable
h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorTable.description: The table represents the list of sensors.

h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorEntry.name: h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorEntry
h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorEntry.description: Each entry contains possible sensor information of WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorRadioId.name: h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorRadioId
h3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorRadioId.description: Represents on which radio the sensor AP detected the AP.

h3cWIPSDctAPRptRSSI.name: h3cWIPSDctAPRptRSSI
h3cWIPSDctAPRptRSSI.description: Represents the current value of signal strength that WIPS sensor AP received from the AP.

h3cWIPSDctAPLastRptTm.name: h3cWIPSDctAPLastRptTm
h3cWIPSDctAPLastRptTm.description: Represents the time that AP was detected by this sensor for the last time since system is up.

h3cWIPSDctStaTable.name: h3cWIPSDctStaTable
h3cWIPSDctStaTable.description: The table represents the list of possible information for stations detected by the WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctStaEntry.name: h3cWIPSDctStaEntry
h3cWIPSDctStaEntry.description: Each entry contains possible station information of each station detected by WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctStaVSD.name: h3cWIPSDctStaVSD
h3cWIPSDctStaVSD.description: Represents the virtual security domain in which the station was detected.

h3cWIPSDctStaMac.name: h3cWIPSDctStaMac
h3cWIPSDctStaMac.description: Represents the MAC address of station.

h3cWIPSDctStaAssocBSSID.name: h3cWIPSDctStaAssocBSSID
h3cWIPSDctStaAssocBSSID.description: Represents the BSSID which station associates with.

h3cWIPSDctStaStatus.name: h3cWIPSDctStaStatus
h3cWIPSDctStaStatus.description: Represents the status of this station detected by WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctStaCategory.name: h3cWIPSDctStaCategory
h3cWIPSDctStaCategory.description: Represents the categorized result of the station.

h3cWIPSDctStaRadioType.name: h3cWIPSDctStaRadioType
h3cWIPSDctStaRadioType.description: Represents the radio type used by the detected station.

h3cWIPSDctStaWorkChannel.name: h3cWIPSDctStaWorkChannel
h3cWIPSDctStaWorkChannel.description: Represents on which radio channel that WIPS sensor AP detected the station.

h3cWIPSDctStaIsCountered.name: h3cWIPSDctStaIsCountered
h3cWIPSDctStaIsCountered.description: Represents whether the detected station is countered by WIPS.

h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2BlackList.name: h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2BlackList
h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2BlackList.description: Represents whether the station will be taken as a rogue station. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into h3cWIPSBlockListTable and the category of the station will be taken as rogue. If the value is false, nothing will be done. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2WhiteList.name: h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2WhiteList
h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2WhiteList.description: Represents whether the station will be taken as an authorized station. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into h3cWIPSTrustListTable. If the value is false, nothing will be done. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2IgnoreList.name: h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2IgnoreList
h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2IgnoreList.description: Represents whether the station will be taken as an ignored station. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into h3cWIPSIgnoreListTable. If the value is false, nothing will be done. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2CtmList.name: h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2CtmList
h3cWIPSDctStaAdd2CtmList.description: Represents whether the station will be taken as a countered station. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into h3cWIPSCountermeasureListTable. If the value is false, nothing will be done. It will return false for get operation.

h3cWIPSDctNetworkCfg.name: h3cWIPSDctNetworkCfg
h3cWIPSDctNetworkCfg.description: Represents the encrypt method, security suite and authentication method which are used by the detected ESS. The lowest 8 bits mean encrypt method. The higher 8 bits mean security suite. The third 8 bits stand for authentication method. The higerest 8 bits are reserved. The meaning is shown as follows: 31 23 15 7 0 + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + | reserved | auth method | security suite|encryptmethod| + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + For encrypt method, the following values are supported: 1: none - clear text or no cipher method is configure, 2: wep - WEP key, 4: tkip - WPA Temporal Key encryption, 8: ccmp - WPA AES CCMP encryption For security suite, the following values are supported: 0x01: clear 0x02: wpa2 0x04: wpa 0x08: wep For authentication method, the following values are supported: 1: none - No key management mode configured, 2: psk - pre-shared key authentication, 3: dot1x - 802.1x authentication. 4: other - other authentication
